==Demographics==
As of recent estimates, Caberfae has about 64 residents, a sharp decline from 72 in 2020 — making it one of the smallest census-designated places in Michigan.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Caberfae, MI {{!}} Data USA|url=https://datausa.io/profile/geo/caberfae-mi|website=datausa.io|access-date=2025-12-01|language=en}}</ref> Its median age is 63.5 years, far higher than average — indicating an older population overall.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Census profile: Caberfae, MI|url=http://censusreporter.org/profiles/16000US2612290-caberfae-mi/|website=Census Reporter|access-date=2025-12-01|language=en}}</ref> The residents are overwhelmingly White and U.S.-born, with 100% identifying as non-Hispanic White and 100% citizens.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Data USA|url=https://datausa.io/profile/geo/caberfae-mi%5D|website=datausa.io|access-date=2025-12-01|language=en}}</ref>

Economically, the community shows modest but stable conditions: median household income is around $58,000, and per-capita income about $41,252.<ref name=":0" /> The poverty rate remains low at just over 3%, well below state and national levels.<ref name=":1" /> Homeownership is universal: virtually all housing units are owner-occupied, and the median property value is about $160,700.<ref name=":1" />{{US Census population
